<#
.SYNOPSIS
    Downloads drivers via WU API and prepares user-facing notification workflow.

.DESCRIPTION
    Main orchestrator for CW RMM. Writes companion scripts to disk from
    embedded content, downloads driver updates (no install), registers
    infrastructure, and starts the notification workflow.

    ARCHITECTURE (v5.8.x): Companion scripts are EMBEDDED in this orchestrator
    and written to disk at runtime using single-quoted here-strings. No S3
    download dependency for companion scripts.

.AUTHOR
    Ken Kruis

.VERSION
    5.8.3

.CHANGELOG
    5.8.3 - Protocol handler changed from CMD to PowerShell launcher.
            Toast button now launches Request-DriverInstall.ps1, which uses
            Start-ScheduledTask to trigger the SYSTEM install task.
            Updated logging text to match the new trigger path.
    5.8.2 - Fixed UserInitiated elevation issue. Protocol handler now triggers
            i3_DriverInstallAndRestart scheduled task (runs as SYSTEM) instead
            of launching the installer script directly as the interactive user.
            Installer bumped to v3.5.4: UserInitiated flag now set by task
            argument so SYSTEM-run still shows user-friendly toast messaging.
            No UAC prompt required; button click is instant and reliable.
    5.8.1 - Embedded installer bumped to v3.5.3: fixes recursive protocol log
            echo (read -> delete -> then echo). Toast repetition duration set
            to 30 days. Embedded scripts use exact source with full original
            comments preserved.
    5.8.0 - Companion scripts embedded (no S3 download). All Write-Log calls
            use -f format operator. Parse check retained as safety net.
#>

[CmdletBinding()]
param
(
    [string]$BasePath           = "C:\ProgramData\i3",
    [int]$NotifyIntervalHours   = 4,
    [int]$NotifyMaxDays         = 30,
    [string]$ToastCaption       = "i3 Updates Available",
    [switch]$Silent,
    [int]$LogRetentionDays      = 30
)

